** About us **

You will enjoy our flexible working arrangements. You will also be working in
a supportive team environment exposing you to all areas of the business. There
are ample opportunities for skill development and growth, allowing you to
maximise your potential.

** Qualifications & experience **

  * Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, information systems, business technology or other relevant degree qualification is desirable. 
  * High level of computing skills, including Word, Excel, Outlook; SharePoint, MS Project, MS Teams, Azure DevOps. 
  * Proven experience in software implementation, technical consulting, or a similar client-facing role. 
  * Strong problem-solving skills with the ability to analyse complex technical issues and provide effective solutions. 
  * Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to interact confidently with clients and internal teams. 
  * Self-motivated and results-driven attitude with a passion for technology and process improvement. 
  * The following will be highly regarded: o Understanding of project management processes. o Proficiency in working with enterprise software solutions, preferably in asset-intensive industries. o Business acumen and good understanding of Mining, Renewable Energy, Gas & Oil practices, and processes. 

** Tasks & responsibilities **

  * Collaborate with clients to understand their unique operational needs and challenges including facilitating client workshops. 
  * Lead the solution approach for our Obzervr Enterprise Mobility platform, ensuring a quality outcome. 
  * Develop project-related technical documentation, e.g., Technical Specification, High-level Design 
  * Conduct thorough system configurations and customisations to align the platform with clients' specific requirements. 
  * Provide or coordinate comprehensive training and support to clients' end-users, ensuring a seamless transition to the digital platform. 
  * Understand the business impact of any technical issues, working closely with the technical support team to provide timely resolutions. 
  * Serve as a product expert and trusted advisor to clients, offering guidance on best practices and optimisation strategies. 
  * Continuously gather feedback from clients and communicate their needs to the product development team for continuous improvement. 
  * Work hand-in-hand with the assigned Delivery Manager and have the agility to lead the delivery for smaller technical change requests. 
  * Deliver our solutions to the highest standards, working closely with our clients and partners. 

** Benefits **

  * Flexible Working Arrangements - Hybrid 
  * Ample opportunities for skill development and growth 
  * Supportive team environment 

